^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 290 - April 1, 2002^*N 
 ^*BApril Fool's Day Edition^*N }
^-
This week's deal was played by ^*BBridge Base Inc.^*N President ^*BFred Gitelman^*N in a practice game just before the start of the 2002 IOC Grand Prix in Salt Lake City. Fred and partner ^*BJoey Silver^*N faced their teammates ^*BNick Gartaganis^*N and ^*BPeter Jones^*N when this week's deal was played. Those 4 along with ^*BKeith Balcombe^*N and ^*BGord Campbell^*N were part of the Canadian team that won the Gold Medal in Salt Lake City. A detailed account of Fred's experiences at the IOC Grand Prix can be found in ^*BDeals of the Week^*N 283 through 288 (available through this web site).

The finals of the San Diego edition of the ^*BBridge Pro Tour^*N will be broadcast live through ^*BBridge Base Online^*N starting this Wednesday at 12 PM EST (17:00 GMT). Access to this broadcast is 100% ^*Bfree^*N. Fred Gitelman will be providing the play-by-play commentary. All bridge players are welcome to attend.

We are planning on producing several more live broadcasts of major tournaments this year including the ^*BCavendish Invitational^*N, the ^*BUSA Team Trials^*N, and the ^*BSwedish National Championships^*N. The times and dates of these broadcasts will be announced through future ^*BDeals of the Week^*N. In order to watch these productions, you must download and install the software for ^*BBridge Base Online^*N. You can download the program to install ^*BBridge Base Online^*N on your PC through the following web page. Click on the blue rectangle below to be taken directly to this web page in a new browser window.

