nt|The main lesson to be learned from this deal is that when a contract seems hopeless, running a long suit can sometimes have unexpected good results. The defenders cannot see all 52 cards. As such, they sometimes make less than optimal discards. Even when all the cards are known, expert players have been known to make the occasional technical error.|
