nt|On some deals (like this one) there is nothing that the defense can do to get out of their own way. Here Peter and Nick discarded as well as they possibly could, but there was no way for the defense to prevent Fred from winning a spade trick at the end. |
pg| ***** 50 ***** |


nt|It is not always necessary to visualize the end position when you start running a long suit. Fred had no idea what was going to happen on this deal until he had played his second last trump. However, he did know that he had nothing to lose by adopting the strategy that he did. It turned out that he had something to gain - an unexpected 10th trick. |
